m</i>."]}]},{"name":"Eudes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of Croatian and Slovenian <b>Rudež</b>: nickname derived from <i>rud</i> ‘red, reddish’, or, alternatively, from <i>rud</i> ‘curly’ (standard Slovenian <i>rod</i>; compare   Rodes  ). In Croatia, the surname is also found in the form <b>Rudeš</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodes","meanings":["Catalan (<b>Rodés</b>): habitational name from any of several places called Rodés, mainly those in El Pallars and El Conflent districts, in northern Catalonia.","Catalan: variant of   Roda  , from Catalan <i>rodes</i>, plural of <i>roda</i> ‘wheel’.","English: variant of   Rhodes  . Compare   Rhode  ."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Firm and resolute’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eudes II de Lannoy was born in 1149, in Lys-lez-Lannoy, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Eudes de LANNOY de la LYS, was 37 and his mother, Blanche de Wavrin, was 26. He had at least 1 son with Blanche de Merville. He died in 1208, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1149–1208":"1149–1208","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1165–1219":"1165–1219","1182–1212":"1182–1212","1112–1179":"1112–1179","1123–1174":"1123–1174","1165":"1165","1174":"1174","1182":"1182","1149":"1149","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1123":"1123","1112":"1112","1144":"1144","Abt 1182":"umbes 1182","1209":"1209","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","Lys-lez-Lannoy, 59367, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Lys-lez-Lannoy, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Lys-lez Lannoy, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Lys-lez-Lannoy, Nord, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1149–1208":"1149–1208","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1165–1219":"1165–1219","1182–1212":"1182–1212","1112–1179":"1112–1179","1123–1174":"1123–1174","1165":"1165","1174":"1174","1182":"1182","1149":"1149","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","